        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 1:27AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 127 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles southeast of Salina to 4 miles east of
Scraper. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Lake Francis...                   Jay...
Rose...                           Kansas...
Lake Eucha State Park...          Snowdale State Park...
Ballard...                        Spavinaw State Park...
Siloam Springs...                 Colcord...
Leach...                          Hoot Owl...
Chloeta...                        Salina...
Scraper...                        Twin Oaks...
Spavinaw...                       Watts...
West Siloam Springs...            Oaks...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for northwestern
Arkansas...and northeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
